article.headline: UTEP 69, Panhandle State 44
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Jason Williams scored 18 points and Omar Thomas added 17 to lead Texas-El Paso to a 69-44 victory over Panhandle State on Sunday. Williams hit 6-of-9 from the field, including both of his 3-pointers, and hit all four of his free throws, but he committed 11 turnovers. Panhandle State couldn't capitalize, however, getting only 10 points off turnovers. Thomas was 5-of-12 from the field and 7-of-9 from the free throw line. He also had 10 rebounds for UTEP (5-2). Eddie Moss led Panhandle State (2-9) with 17 points, 15 of those on 3-pointers. UTEP scored 21 points off Panhandle State's 17 turnovers. UTEP shot 46 percent from the field to 28 percent for Panhandle State. The Miners led 37-21 at the half.
